{{Orphan|date=July 2015}}
'''Janzouri''' or '''Janzuri''' or '''Zanzuri''' or '''Zanzouri''' or '''Ganzouri''' or '''Ganzuri''' is a family name derived from the name ({{lang-ar|جَنْزُور}} {{transl|ar|''Janzūr''}}) (and zanzur ({{lang-ar|زَنْزُور}} {{transl|ar|''zanzūr''}}) is same of janzur but in [[Libyan Arabic|Libyan dialect]] the [[ج|ǧīm]] change to [[ز|zayn]], and ganzur is same of Janzur but the ǧīm is [[Voiced velar stop]]), these families reside in [[Libya]], [[Egypt]], [[Israel]] and [[Italy]], the families that reside in Israel and Italy Jews origin from the city of [[Janzour]], Libya, moved from Libya to Israel at 1949<ref>http://megafon-news.co.il/asys/archives/195065</ref><ref>http://jewishrefugees.blogspot.com/2011/04/forgotten-exodus-tellls-its-story.html</ref> and the rest moved to Italy at 1969.
== People with surname == [[Kamal Ganzouri]], He served as [[Prime Minister of Egypt]] from January 2, 1996 until October 5, 1999, and served the position again from November 25, 2011 until August 2, 2012.
