'''Reavis Falls''' is a seasonal [[waterfall]] located within the [[Superstition Mountains]] in [[Arizona]].<ref name=Waterfalls>{{cite web|title=Most People Don't Know These 12 Waterfalls Are Hiding Here In Arizona|url=http://www.onlyinyourstate.com/arizona/waterfalls-az/|website=OnlyInYourState|accessdate=27 January 2016|language=en-US}}</ref> The falls are named after Elisha Marcus Reavis,<ref name=ReavisFalls>{{cite web|title=Maiden Prayer Glen (Reavis Fall) |url=http://superstitionmountaintomkollenborn.blogspot.com/2009/12/maiden-prayer-glen-reavis-fall.html|website=Tom Kollenborn Chronicles|accessdate=18 April 2016|language=en-US}}</ref> who had a ranch, farm, and orchard in the Superstition Mountains a few miles south of the falls.

