:'' Snowfield is also a former name of the UK indie rock band [[Editors (band)|Editors]]''
[[File:Tarn_6320_feet_23126.JPG|right|thumb|Meltwater from snowfields fill [[tarns]] on [[Mount Rainier]].]]
A '''snow field''', '''snowfield ''' or '''neve''' is an accumulation of [[permanent snow]] and ice, typically found above the [[snow line]], normally in [[mountain|mountainous]] and [[glacier|glacial]] terrain.

[[Glacier#Formation|Glaciers]] originate in snowfields. The lower end of a glacier is usually free from snow and [[névé]] in summer. In the upper end and above the upper boundary of a glacier, the snow field is an [[ice field]] covered with snow. The glacier upper boundary, where it emerges from under a snow field, is ill-defined because of gradual transition.<ref>Thomas Chrowder Chamberlin, Rollin D. Salisbury (1904) "Geology", [https://books.google.com/books?id=p0QNAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA258&dq=%22snow+field+is%22 p. 258] <!-- a more modern reference would be preferred here --></ref>

